<TITLE>Johannes Kepler</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ID="1594.1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 (December 27, 1571 - November 15, 1630), a key figure in the scientific revolution, was a German mathematician, astronomer, astrologer, and an early writer of science fiction stories. 
<REF ID="1594.2" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">He</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 is best known for 
<REF ID="1594.3" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Johannes Kepler's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Kepler's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 laws of planetary motion, based on 
<REF ID="1594.4" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Johannes Kepler's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Kepler's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 works Astronomia nova, Harmonice Mundi and the textbook Epitome of Copernican Astronomy.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
Through 
<REF ID="1594.5" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="subj-det">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Johannes Kepler's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="genitive">Kepler's</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="genitive">his</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="genitive">whose</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 career 
<REF ID="1594.6" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler</REFEX>
<ALT-REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Johannes Kepler himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="name" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="nominal" CASE="plain">Kepler himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="empty">_</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">he himself</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who</REFEX>
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="yes" HEAD="rel-pron" CASE="nominative">who himself</REFEX>
</ALT-REFEX>
</REF>
 was a mathematics teacher at a Graz seminary school (later the University of Graz, Austria), an assistant to Tycho Brahe, court mathematician to Emperor Rudolf II, mathematics teacher in Linz, Austria, and court astrologer to General Wallenstein. 
<REF ID="1594.7" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np-subj">
<REFEX REG08-TYPE="pronoun" EMPHATIC="no" HEAD="pronoun" CASE="nominative">He</REFEX>
